{'id': 22046901, 'body': 'Hi,
The permission in Forest is needed only to operate the mechanism of Forest itself. We have strictly followed the GDPR rule and regulation. Please refer to out permission explained: http://help.forestapp.cc/forest-faq-english-version/android/access-permission-purposes

Feel free to contact us again if you have further questions or suggestion. :)', 'modified': '2021-04-05T09:36:49Z'}

{'id': 32229160, 'body': "Hi,
Sorry to hear you've hit this. It's most likely because of iOS crashes that the exceeded time doesn't count for you. These crashes have been found in iOS 12 onwards where apps usually get killed (by the iOS system) and have to restart themselves after users switch to a different app and then switch back, as well as where users tend to find themselves on the home screen of the device after they leave an app in the foreground, lock the screen and then unlock it in a while.

As the issue is from Apple's end, we regret to say that there's nothing we could do to on our end at the moment, but we'll keep seeking a way around this. Besides, regarding the second problem, would you please include a video and email us at support@forestapp.cc so that we can look into the problem further? We will be glad to provide assistance. Thank you!", 'modified': '2022-09-26T09:04:15Z'}

