{'id': 5787872, 'body': 'Hi,

Since the cost of planting real trees is covered by the company, complications can arise when users plant too many real trees; the cost can easily exceed the app’s revenue.  Therefore, the amount of real trees users can plant will be limited.  

Feel free to contact us if you have further questions. :) - Forest', 'modified': '2018-11-03T12:43:52Z'}

{'id': 4832461, 'body': 'Hello,

We have considered adding this feature, but have not come up with a good way to implement at this time. 

Feel free to drop us a line via our in-app feedback system if you have further questions. :) - Forest', 'modified': '2018-08-28T01:53:09Z'}

{'id': 17387674, 'body': 'Hi,
Since the cost of planting real trees is donated by the company, we have to limit the amount of real trees every user can plant, or we will be running out of budget soon and forced to halt the tree-planting campaign.

Thank you for contacting us and for your contribution to the environment. :)', 'modified': '2020-08-20T01:21:31Z'}

